        "content": "To address DigitalWellbeing's concerns, while there are challenges related to mental health, social media platforms are increasingly implementing tools to promote healthy usage, such as screen time trackers and mental health resources. Furthermore, social media's ability to connect individuals can also provide support networks, enabling users to share experiences and find community-driven solutions. Regarding PrivacyAdvocate's points, it's important to recognize that social media companies are improving transparency and user control over data. Users now have more options to manage privacy settings, and ongoing regulatory efforts are pushing companies towards better data practices, ensuring privacy concerns are progressively addressed.",
