      {
        "content": "TechOptimist's argument that social media democratizes access and fosters connectivity overlooks the significant mental health challenges these platforms pose. While social media can empower, the addictive nature of its design often leads to increased anxiety and depression, negating potential benefits. The screen time tools mentioned are not effective enough to counteract the deep-rooted issues in platform algorithms designed to maximize engagement. Without comprehensive reforms focused on mental health, any empowerment provided by social media will be compromised by the detrimental effects on users' well-being. The need for reform is urgent to balance connectivity with mental health protection.",
